Description: One of the two original haplotypes of the pandemic (A and B). Many sequences originating from China and many global exports; including to South East Asia Japan South Korea Australia the USA and Europe represented in this lineage
Mostly Spanish lineage now includes South and Central American sequences, other European countries and Kazakhstan.
Costa Rica lineage from pango-designation issue #33
Predominantly Ecuador lineage, from pango-designation issue #168

A lineage with a lot of representation from Spanish-speaking countries. A Spanish/ South-American lineage, but now with sequences from an outbreak in Scotland. Also now includes what was previously A.10.
International lineage with a number of variants of potential biological concern, including 681R

Mayotte/ European cluster with 18 changes in the long branch leading to this cluster, including 7 NS changes in the spike (L18F, L452R, N501Y, A653V, H655Y, D796Y, G1219V), on a 614D background. pango-designation issue #11.
This lineage has 9 changes on its basal branch, including the 69-70del, N501T (not Y) and H655Y. (This variant is picked up by the qPCR S drop). pango-designation issue #12
Lineage circulating in multiple countries from pango-designation issue #78
Lineage in several countries, associated with travel from Tanzania, from pango-designation issue #138
One of the two original haplotypes of the pandemic(and first to be discovered)
A large European lineage the origin of which roughly corresponds to the Northern Italian outbreak early in 2020.
